The paper deals with encoding and decoding methods for codes that correct tandem duplications in DNA sequences. This involves the study of finite state encoders and ranking/unranking algorithms for irreducible words. These topics are closely related to information theory (cs.IT), data structures (cs.DS), discrete mathematics (cs.DM), computational complexity (cs.CC), and computational biology (cs.SI).
